Build Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/OperatingModelEditor.tsx

This is the primary editing surface for operating models — a document-style text editor where prose IS the spec.

First read:
- Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/dashboard.css (understand existing styles)
- Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/config.ts (APP_CONFIG)

The component renders:

1. Header bar: editable name input, status badge (DRAFT|COMPILING|LIVE|ERROR), amber [Commit] button, back arrow button

2. Prose display area: a div that renders compiled prose with colored inline spans for references:
   - @references → <span class='om-ref om-ref--integration'>@gmail/inbox</span>
   - #references → <span class='om-ref om-ref--object'>#contact/email</span>  
   - {variables} → <span class='om-ref om-ref--variable'>{priority}</span>
   - kebab-agent-names → <span class='om-ref om-ref--agent'>triage-agent</span>
   Clicking any span calls onReferenceClick with the ref data
   Below the rendered prose: a plain textarea where users can edit the raw prose (shown when compileStatus === 'idle' or no compiledProse)
   The textarea has a 500ms debounce that calls onProseChange

3. Unresolved references warning: yellow box listing unresolved refs if unresolved.length > 0

4. Execution section at bottom (only if executionData provided):
   - processedToday count, lastRunAgo, triggerDescription
   - recentRuns as a list with green/red dot + label + ago

Typescript props:
```typescript
interface Reference {
  id: string;
  type: 'integration' | 'object' | 'variable' | 'agent';
  slug: string;
  span?: [number, number];
  config?: Record<string, unknown>;
  resolved?: boolean;
}

interface OperatingModelEditorProps {
  workflowId?: string;
  name?: string;
  initialProse?: string;
  compiledProse?: string;
  references?: Reference[];
  unresolved?: string[];
  executionData?: {
    processedToday: number;
    recentRuns: Array<{id: string; status: string; ago: string; label: string}>;
    lastRunAgo?: string;
    triggerDescription?: string;
  };
  compileStatus?: 'idle' | 'compiling' | 'compiled' | 'error';
  onProseChange?: (prose: string) => void;
  onReferenceClick?: (ref: Reference) => void;
  onCommit?: (name: string, prose: string) => void;
  onBack?: () => void;
}
```

The renderCompiledProse function: take compiledProse string, use regex to find @[\w/]+, #[\w/{}.]+, \{[^}]+\}, and known agent names (kebab-case words not preceded by @ or #). Use dangerouslySetInnerHTML only on a string you build by replacing those patterns with <span> tags. Escape the rest of the HTML.

