Build Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/ReferencePopover.tsx

A floating popover rendered at document.body level (via React portal) when a user clicks a @reference, #reference, {variable}, or agent name in the operating model editor.

First read:
- Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/dashboard/dashboard.css (existing styles)

Props:
```typescript
interface Reference {
  id: string;
  type: 'integration' | 'object' | 'variable' | 'agent';
  slug: string;
  config?: Record<string, unknown>;
  resolved?: boolean;
}

interface ReferencePopoverProps {
  reference: Reference | null;
  anchorRect?: DOMRect | null;
  onClose: () => void;
  onConfigChange?: (slug: string, config: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
}
```

Render different content per type:

**Integration** (`@gmail/search`):
- Header: icon + slug + 'Integration' label + close button  
- Auth status: green 'Connected' or amber 'Configure'
- Capability description if resolved
- Input fields for any required args (from config)

**Object** (`#contact/email`):
- Header: slug + 'Object Type' label + close button
- Field list (from config.fields if available, otherwise generic description)
- Description of what data it provides

**Variable** (`{priority: P1|P2|P3}`):
- Header: variable name + 'Variable' label + close button
- Show current options as chips
- Add option: small input + Enter to add
- Delete option: × on each chip
- onChange calls onConfigChange with updated options

**Agent** (`triage-agent`):
- Header: agent name (editable input) + 'Agent' label + close button
- Model: readonly badge showing inferred route (auto/build etc)
- System prompt: textarea (4 rows) for custom instructions, calls onConfigChange on blur
- Temperature: hidden by default, 'Advanced' toggle to show (slider 0-1)

Positioning: position fixed, top = anchorRect.bottom + 8, left = anchorRect.left. Cap left so it doesn't go off-screen (use Math.min(left, window.innerWidth - 360 - 16)). Cap top similarly.

Click outside to close: useEffect that listens for mousedown on document, if target is not inside the popover, call onClose.

